WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
♪♪

2
00:00:06.858 --> 00:00:09.583
NOLAN: Swear to God. now
he has this woman tied up.

3
00:00:09.585 --> 00:00:11.251
his own aunt.

4
00:00:11.253 --> 00:00:13.153
He has a shotgun rigged
with duct tape and a string

5
00:00:13.155 --> 00:00:14.621
so he can shoot her from the fireplace.

6
00:00:14.623 --> 00:00:17.658
Yeah. while Chen's across town
going toe-to-toe with the 5-4.

7
00:00:17.660 --> 00:00:19.459
Yeah. thirty gang members
against me and my T.O.

8
00:00:19.461 --> 00:00:20.922
[CHUCKLES] Oh. my God. that's hardcore.

9
00:00:20.924 --> 00:00:21.956
How the hell'd you get out of that?

10
00:00:21.958 --> 00:00:25.018
No joke. my T.O. goes.
"When you're in the LAPD"...

11
00:00:25.020 --> 00:00:26.486
TOGETHER: "You're never alone".

12
00:00:26.488 --> 00:00:27.660
And right on cue.

13
00:00:27.662 --> 00:00:29.489
- an airship arrives with a SWAT team.
- [LAUGHING]

14
00:00:29.491 --> 00:00:30.757
Damn. there's me thinking

15
00:00:30.759 --> 00:00:32.892
discharging my weapon
this year was a big deal.

16
00:00:32.894 --> 00:00:34.527
Aw. don't beat yourself up. Chris.

17
00:00:34.529 --> 00:00:35.895
I'm sure someday you'll catch up.

18
00:00:35.897 --> 00:00:37.620
[ALL MURMURING]

19
00:00:37.622 --> 00:00:38.678
Oh. it's like that?

20
00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:40.066
Oh. yeah. It's like that.

21
00:00:40.068 --> 00:00:42.135
Come on. you guys. We're
not in the Academy anymore.

22
00:00:42.137 --> 00:00:44.191
We don't have to be
competitive about everything.

23
00:00:44.193 --> 00:00:46.608
Well. it's not a competition
when I always win.

24
00:00:46.610 --> 00:00:48.752
- [GROUP "OH" S]
- Ooh. that's a deep cut! But he does have a point.

25
00:00:48.754 --> 00:00:49.776
- That's it. West.
- Hmm?

26
00:00:49.778 --> 00:00:51.211
You and me. right now...

27
00:00:51.213 --> 00:00:52.979
We're gonna settle this
thing once and for all.

28
00:00:52.981 --> 00:00:54.147
Mm.

29
00:00:54.149 --> 00:00:56.950
[CHEERING. LAUGHTER]

30
00:00:56.952 --> 00:00:58.218
Drink up. Drink up.

31
00:00:58.220 --> 00:00:59.352
[CHEERING]

32
00:00:59.354 --> 00:01:02.082
I can't believe they still
can't let go of their rivalry.

33
00:01:02.084 --> 00:01:04.608
Can't you? They were first
and second at the Academy.

34
00:01:04.610 --> 00:01:05.959
Their dads were first and second.

35
00:01:05.961 --> 00:01:07.760
- Oh! Sorry! Sorry!
- Oh. ho. ho!

36
00:01:07.762 --> 00:01:08.929
- [CHUCKLING] You okay?
- Yep.

37
00:01:09.931 --> 00:01:10.997
Nope.

38
00:01:10.999 --> 00:01:13.666
I was just gonna get some
air. How about you join me?

39
00:01:13.668 --> 00:01:15.135
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

40
00:01:15.137 --> 00:01:16.970
- Sorry.
- No. no. no. Don't.

41
00:01:16.972 --> 00:01:19.006
[CHEERING]

42
00:01:20.242 --> 00:01:22.575
ERIN: So. I'm actually fine.

43
00:01:22.577 --> 00:01:24.978
Just... a little worried about Chris.

44
00:01:24.980 --> 00:01:27.480
I mean. you always gave the
best advice at the Academy.

45
00:01:27.482 --> 00:01:29.333
Thank you. Uh. what's going on?

46
00:01:29.335 --> 00:01:31.710
At first. I thought it was
just a rocky transition.

47
00:01:31.712 --> 00:01:34.002
You know. going from
being top of the class

48
00:01:34.004 --> 00:01:35.160
to being just another Boot.

49
00:01:35.162 --> 00:01:38.258
But... he never really evened out.

50
00:01:38.260 --> 00:01:40.693
Did you know he barely
passed our six-month exam?

51
00:01:40.695 --> 00:01:42.629
- Can you believe that?
- Actually. I <i>can.</i>

52
00:01:42.631 --> 00:01:44.597
If he came in expecting it to be easy.

53
00:01:44.599 --> 00:01:45.832
I mean. it is <i>not.</i>

54
00:01:45.834 --> 00:01:48.301
I'm worried. What if he's
really not ready?

55
00:01:48.303 --> 00:01:49.602
Should I say something?

56
00:01:49.604 --> 00:01:51.605
I can't answer that for you.

57
00:01:52.936 --> 00:01:56.338
I can tell you that this year has
been tough for <i>all</i> of us.

58
00:01:56.340 --> 00:01:58.673
I mean. no vacation. no sick days.

59
00:01:58.675 --> 00:02:00.308
constantly under a microscope.

60
00:02:00.310 --> 00:02:01.810
We've <i>all</i> stumbled.

61
00:02:01.812 --> 00:02:03.645
Yeah.

62
00:02:03.647 --> 00:02:05.814
If I were you. I would just...

63
00:02:05.816 --> 00:02:07.682
tell Chris you're there for him.

64
00:02:07.684 --> 00:02:10.018
And if he can bear down
for one more month.

65
00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:11.486
then he can take some time off

66
00:02:11.488 --> 00:02:13.655
and just clear his
head. you know. reset.

67
00:02:13.657 --> 00:02:16.825
I've been trying to convince
him to go on the road with me.

68
00:02:16.827 --> 00:02:19.961
take an RV and camp. hike.

69
00:02:19.963 --> 00:02:22.130
just disconnect from all the noise

70
00:02:22.132 --> 00:02:23.498
before we come back as P2s.

71
00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:24.700
See. that would be perfect.

72
00:02:25.669 --> 00:02:27.435
Yeah.

73
00:02:27.437 --> 00:02:28.837
Thanks.

74
00:02:28.839 --> 00:02:31.039
I knew I'd feel better talking to you.

75
00:02:31.041 --> 00:02:32.607
50 bucks.

76
00:02:32.609 --> 00:02:34.076
Nolan! I need your help.

77
00:02:34.912 --> 00:02:36.511
NOLAN: I'm sorry. How is this helping?

78
00:02:36.513 --> 00:02:38.980
- Jackson and I are tied.
- One more event will settle this.

79
00:02:38.982 --> 00:02:40.615
If you hit Nolan. you lose.

80
00:02:40.617 --> 00:02:41.850
Wait. what game is this?

81
00:02:41.852 --> 00:02:43.151
- Suicide darts.
- Suicide darts.

82
00:02:43.153 --> 00:02:44.519
Ow!

83
00:02:44.521 --> 00:02:47.789
[ALARM CLOCK RINGING]

84
00:02:47.791 --> 00:02:49.724
[RINGING STOPS]

85
00:02:49.726 --> 00:02:52.060
I do not wanna go to work today.

86
00:02:52.062 --> 00:02:54.689
EMMETT: Mm. you can
be a few minutes late.

87
00:02:54.691 --> 00:02:56.431
- [SCOFFS]
- [GRUNTS]

88
00:02:56.433 --> 00:02:57.465
[GROANS]

89
00:02:57.467 --> 00:03:00.735
Yeah. and do push-ups
in between every call

90
00:03:00.737 --> 00:03:02.377
and jog behind the shop?

91
00:03:02.379 --> 00:03:03.535
No. thanks.

92
00:03:03.537 --> 00:03:04.706
Mm.

93
00:03:04.708 --> 00:03:06.215
- Oh. come on!
- Mnh-mnh!

94
00:03:06.217 --> 00:03:07.339
Bradford's chill.

95
00:03:07.341 --> 00:03:09.711
I mean. maybe if you're
playing pick-up with him.

96
00:03:09.713 --> 00:03:12.013
but not when he's your T.O.

97
00:03:12.015 --> 00:03:14.516
He once designed an IED

98
00:03:14.518 --> 00:03:16.818
to blow up baby powder in my face

99
00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:17.886
just to make a point.

100
00:03:17.888 --> 00:03:19.487
Is he allowed to do that?

101
00:03:19.489 --> 00:03:21.038
I just need to get through
the next thirty days.

102
00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:22.590
and then I will be free.

103
00:03:22.592 --> 00:03:24.926
No more mind games. No more Tim Tests.

104
00:03:24.928 --> 00:03:26.828
No more chewing me out in public.

105
00:03:26.830 --> 00:03:29.998
Okay. so you're saying thirty days.

106
00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:32.167
and <i>then</i> I can make you late?

107
00:03:32.169 --> 00:03:33.602
- Mm.
- Hm?

108
00:03:34.571 --> 00:03:36.171
Mm.

109
00:03:36.173 --> 00:03:37.906
Um... listen.

110
00:03:37.908 --> 00:03:40.208
If we bump into each other at work.

111
00:03:40.210 --> 00:03:43.578
can we please just play it cool?

112
00:03:43.580 --> 00:03:44.879
I'm not cool?

113
00:03:44.881 --> 00:03:46.514
No! You know what I mean!

114
00:03:46.516 --> 00:03:49.507
Like. on the... D.L.

115
00:03:49.509 --> 00:03:50.585
The D.L.?

116
00:03:50.587 --> 00:03:52.347
Yep. I said that. I'm sorry.

117
00:03:52.349 --> 00:03:54.789
[LAUGHING] Don't laugh!

118
00:03:54.791 --> 00:03:56.139
Don't you work with your roommate?

119
00:03:56.141 --> 00:03:58.526
Oh. Jackson's got my back.
He would never talk.

120
00:03:58.528 --> 00:04:02.097
Well. I can't promise I'll be
able to keep my eyes off of you.

121
00:04:02.099 --> 00:04:04.966
but otherwise. deal.

122
00:04:04.968 --> 00:04:06.491
- Thank you.
- Mm.

123
00:04:06.493 --> 00:04:07.949
- Aah!
- [BOTH LAUGH]

124
00:04:07.951 --> 00:04:09.604
But. wait. Grace might actually

125
00:04:09.606 --> 00:04:11.072
let her ex-husband come back home?

126
00:04:11.074 --> 00:04:12.640
For the sake of her son.

127
00:04:12.642 --> 00:04:14.542
Look. I-I get where she's coming from.

128
00:04:14.544 --> 00:04:16.444
I mean. I did something
similar with <i>my</i> ex.

129
00:04:16.446 --> 00:04:17.545
Staying together for the kid.

130
00:04:17.547 --> 00:04:19.781
even when you knew
the relationship was doomed.

131
00:04:19.783 --> 00:04:22.050
Did that actually make
things better for Henry?

132
00:04:22.052 --> 00:04:23.718
No. But what am I gonna do?

133
00:04:23.720 --> 00:04:25.415
Mansplain to her she's making a mistake?

134
00:04:25.417 --> 00:04:26.544
How well is that gonna go over?

135
00:04:26.546 --> 00:04:27.622
Yeah. not well.

136
00:04:27.624 --> 00:04:29.557
But if you leave her alone.

137
00:04:29.559 --> 00:04:30.968
you risk giving the ex an opening.

138
00:04:30.970 --> 00:04:32.058
Tough one.

139
00:04:32.060 --> 00:04:33.482
I'm looking for some sage advice here.

140
00:04:33.484 --> 00:04:36.153
If you haven't noticed. my
personal life's a dumpster fire.

141
00:04:37.567 --> 00:04:39.968
All I can say is...

142
00:04:39.970 --> 00:04:41.504
I'm rooting for you two.

143
00:04:42.304 --> 00:04:44.272
Good luck. buddy. [CHUCKLES]

144
00:04:44.274 --> 00:04:45.740
[CLAPS HANDS] You can do it.

145
00:04:45.742 --> 00:04:46.975
I'm telling you. [LAUGHS]

146
00:04:46.977 --> 00:04:50.678
Today is our rookies' one-year
mark in the F.T.O. program.

147
00:04:50.680 --> 00:04:52.981
Congratulations on not washing out.

148
00:04:52.983 --> 00:04:55.050
[CHEERING]

149
00:04:55.052 --> 00:04:56.151
Yet.

150
00:04:56.153 --> 00:04:57.252
We'll see.

151
00:04:57.254 --> 00:04:58.409
There's still time.

152
00:04:58.411 --> 00:05:01.656
That also means today is the start

153
00:05:01.658 --> 00:05:02.991
of your Thirty Day Push.

154
00:05:03.756 --> 00:05:05.236
Why is that important. Officer Nolan?

155
00:05:06.163 --> 00:05:08.129
Because in one month.

156
00:05:08.131 --> 00:05:10.298
we will no longer be
probationary employees.

157
00:05:10.300 --> 00:05:14.602
but fully fledged patrol
officers of the LAPD?

158
00:05:14.604 --> 00:05:16.004
- No.
- Damn it.

159
00:05:16.006 --> 00:05:18.480
SGT. GREY: Because.
as your T.O.s have pointed out.

160
00:05:18.482 --> 00:05:20.141
you are not there yet.

161
00:05:20.143 --> 00:05:22.544
The end of the race
is always the hardest.

162
00:05:22.546 --> 00:05:25.280
The Push is to remind
you not to celebrate

163
00:05:25.282 --> 00:05:26.848
until you cross the finish line.

164
00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:27.949
Understand?

165
00:05:27.951 --> 00:05:29.017
TOGETHER: Yes. sir.

166
00:05:29.019 --> 00:05:30.118
Good.

167
00:05:30.120 --> 00:05:32.720
And... that's all I got.

168
00:05:32.722 --> 00:05:34.956
For the first time in history.

169
00:05:34.958 --> 00:05:36.824
the night shift did their jobs...

170
00:05:36.826 --> 00:05:39.961
left no open cases
that require follow-up.

171
00:05:39.963 --> 00:05:42.630
So. go on. find some crime.

172
00:05:42.632 --> 00:05:43.865
And be safe out there.

173
00:05:43.867 --> 00:05:45.134
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

174
00:05:46.870 --> 00:05:49.304
It's weird we haven't had any calls yet.

175
00:05:49.306 --> 00:05:51.139
Crime doesn't run on a schedule. Boot.

176
00:05:51.141 --> 00:05:54.042
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

177
00:05:54.044 --> 00:05:55.343
What are you so happy about?

178
00:05:55.345 --> 00:05:57.312
What? Nothing.

179
00:05:57.314 --> 00:05:58.646
Can't I smile?

180
00:05:58.648 --> 00:06:00.215
You've just been doing it a lot lately.

181
00:06:00.217 --> 00:06:02.560
I didn't realize happiness
was an impediment

182
00:06:02.562 --> 00:06:03.651
to being a good cop.

183
00:06:03.653 --> 00:06:04.819
I'm just surprised you haven't tried

184
00:06:04.821 --> 00:06:06.888
to talk my ear off about whatever it is.

185
00:06:06.890 --> 00:06:09.124
So. what? Did you rescue a kitten?

186
00:06:09.126 --> 00:06:10.158
Adopt a star?

187
00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:13.661
My personal life is
none of your business.

188
00:06:13.663 --> 00:06:15.563
Finally. There's hope for you yet.

189
00:06:15.565 --> 00:06:16.721
[SCOFFS]

190
00:06:16.723 --> 00:06:18.746
LOPEZ: My mom is driving me crazy.

191
00:06:18.748 --> 00:06:20.335
She's teamed up with Wesley's mom.

192
00:06:20.337 --> 00:06:21.936
so every time I try to make a decision

193
00:06:21.938 --> 00:06:23.204
about the wedding. I'm outnumbered.

194
00:06:23.206 --> 00:06:25.073
You're the bride.
Shouldn't you get final say?

195
00:06:25.075 --> 00:06:26.741
I'm the only girl in either family.

196
00:06:26.743 --> 00:06:28.209
so they're living vicariously.

197
00:06:28.211 --> 00:06:29.911
And I don't have the
bandwidth to push back

198
00:06:29.913 --> 00:06:32.080
because I'm so focused
on making detective.

199
00:06:32.082 --> 00:06:33.881
If I don't make the next
round of promotions.

200
00:06:33.883 --> 00:06:36.784
I'll have to take the
detective's exam again.

201
00:06:36.786 --> 00:06:38.086
But while I'm distracted.

202
00:06:38.088 --> 00:06:39.921
those <i>viejas are hijacking my wedding.</i>

203
00:06:39.923 --> 00:06:41.789
Come on. I'm pretty
sure it's not that bad.

204
00:06:41.791 --> 00:06:45.316
They decided the color scheme
should be pink and peach.

205
00:06:45.318 --> 00:06:46.394
Oh. no.

206
00:06:46.396 --> 00:06:48.763
Do I look like a woman
who's ever worn peach?

207
00:06:48.765 --> 00:06:50.898
No. You're definitely an autumn.

208
00:06:50.900 --> 00:06:52.301
[CHUCKLES]

209
00:06:55.705 --> 00:06:58.106
- [POLICE RADIO CHATTER]
- Is that... ?

210
00:06:58.108 --> 00:06:59.707
No.

211
00:06:59.709 --> 00:07:00.976
No.

212
00:07:02.879 --> 00:07:03.912
Wait a second.

213
00:07:05.248 --> 00:07:06.281
No. Forget it.

214
00:07:06.283 --> 00:07:08.383
Okay. so. how about you
make visual confirmation

215
00:07:08.385 --> 00:07:09.951
<i>before</i> you speak?

216
00:07:09.953 --> 00:07:11.153
Roger that.

217
00:07:12.656 --> 00:07:14.289
You a little nervous about court today?

218
00:07:14.291 --> 00:07:15.323
My lawyer says.

219
00:07:15.325 --> 00:07:17.825
with all of my positive
changes that I've made

220
00:07:17.827 --> 00:07:20.828
and my improved relationship
with Donovan. there's no reason

221
00:07:20.830 --> 00:07:22.730
the judge shouldn't
grant me shared custody.

222
00:07:22.732 --> 00:07:23.765
That's great!

223
00:07:23.767 --> 00:07:25.800
Yeah. except the judge
is a real hard-ass

224
00:07:25.802 --> 00:07:29.404
and has a reputation for being
unorthodox in his rulings.

225
00:07:29.406 --> 00:07:32.741
I'm sure you have
nothing to worry about.

226
00:07:35.278 --> 00:07:38.279
Man! I don't know that I've
ever had a shift this quiet.

227
00:07:38.281 --> 00:07:41.416
[TIRES SCREECH]

228
00:07:41.418 --> 00:07:44.575
Did you really just say
the "Q" word in my shop?

229
00:07:44.577 --> 00:07:45.820
What? Quie...

230
00:07:45.822 --> 00:07:47.755
Na-na-ah-ah-ah-ah! Stop!

231
00:07:47.757 --> 00:07:50.158
You do not. under any circumstance.

232
00:07:50.160 --> 00:07:52.760
<i>ever</i> use the "Q" word while on duty.

233
00:07:52.762 --> 00:07:54.829
That is like saying "Macbeth" in theater

234
00:07:54.831 --> 00:07:56.998
or talking about a
no-hitter in the dugout.

235
00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.434
O... kay. I had no idea
you were superstitious.

236
00:07:59.436 --> 00:08:01.526
That is not superstition. That's fact.

237
00:08:01.528 --> 00:08:03.071
- [SEATBELT CLICKS]
- Where are you going?

238
00:08:03.073 --> 00:08:05.006
I am going to get the
trauma plate for my vest.

239
00:08:05.008 --> 00:08:06.874
'cause I have a feeling
I'm gonna need it.

240
00:08:06.876 --> 00:08:09.811
You and your big mouth probably
just cost me custody of my kid.

241
00:08:09.813 --> 00:08:12.948
[VEHICLE DOOR OPENS. CLOSES]

242
00:08:15.652 --> 00:08:17.385
DISPATCH: <i>Wilshire
units. information only.</i>

243
00:08:17.387 --> 00:08:20.495
<i>Hollywood division is in pursuit
after a shots fired call.</i>

244
00:08:20.497 --> 00:08:22.786
<i>Event 8-0-5 working on channel 4.</i>

245
00:08:22.788 --> 00:08:24.025
<i>- Information only.
- [RADIO BEEPS]</i>

246
00:08:24.027 --> 00:08:25.393
Turn that on. I wanna hear.

247
00:08:25.395 --> 00:08:26.527
[CLICK]

248
00:08:26.529 --> 00:08:28.129
OFFICER: <i>Uh. gr-gray
Maserati. no plates.</i>

249
00:08:28.131 --> 00:08:29.964
- [<i>SIREN WAILING</i>] <i>
- Suspect vehicle is picking up speed.</i>

250
00:08:29.966 --> 00:08:32.867
<i>Uh. we are southbound on
Normandie. 50 miles an hour.</i>

251
00:08:32.869 --> 00:08:34.168
<i>We got moderate traffic.</i>

252
00:08:34.170 --> 00:08:35.870
Wait. That voice.

253
00:08:35.872 --> 00:08:36.971
That's Chris.

254
00:08:36.973 --> 00:08:37.973
Rios.

255
00:08:38.975 --> 00:08:40.475
We went to the Academy together.

256
00:08:40.477 --> 00:08:42.667
His dad worked Narcotics with
my old man back in the day.

257
00:08:42.669 --> 00:08:44.912
Well. at least Hollywood's
getting a little action today.

258
00:08:44.914 --> 00:08:47.215
<i>O-O-O-Okay. wait.
I'm... J-Just stand by.</i>

259
00:08:47.217 --> 00:08:48.349
- [<i>SIREN WAILING</i>]
- Something's going down.

260
00:08:48.351 --> 00:08:49.817
<i>Okay. he's left on Wilshire.</i>

261
00:08:49.819 --> 00:08:51.686
<i>E-Eastbound on Wilshire. Speed is 70.</i>

262
00:08:51.688 --> 00:08:53.921
- [<i>CAR HORN BLARING</i>]
<i>- This is heavy traffic. He's... He's blowing lights.</i>

263
00:08:53.923 --> 00:08:55.890
<i>- Sidewalk! He's on the sidewalk!
- He's too amped up.</i>

264
00:08:55.892 --> 00:08:57.058
DISPATCH: <i>Copy. eastbound Wilshire.</i>

265
00:08:57.060 --> 00:08:58.326
<i>speed 70. blowing lights call.</i>

266
00:08:58.328 --> 00:08:59.894
<i>6-Mary-100. copy?</i>

267
00:08:59.896 --> 00:09:01.396
6-MARY-100: <i>Copy. Advise Mid-Wilshire.</i>

268
00:09:01.398 --> 00:09:03.731
<i>Want is 245 with a handgun.</i>

269
00:09:03.733 --> 00:09:06.067
Control. 7-Adam-15.
attach us to the pursuit.

270
00:09:06.069 --> 00:09:08.403
Event 8-0-5 and switching to channel 4.

271
00:09:08.405 --> 00:09:10.405
- [RADIO BEEPS]
- "Quiet". he says.

272
00:09:10.407 --> 00:09:13.574
<i>6-Adam-41. just T.C.'d.
Wilshire at Virgil.</i>

273
00:09:13.576 --> 00:09:15.943
<i>We are lead car. I-I'm
gonna need backup. guys.</i>

274
00:09:15.945 --> 00:09:17.245
<i>I need... I-I need help!</i>

275
00:09:17.247 --> 00:09:18.946
<i>Copy. 6-Mary-47 help call.</i>

276
00:09:18.948 --> 00:09:20.948
<i>Hollywood and Mid-Wilshire
units responding.</i>

277
00:09:20.950 --> 00:09:23.551
Control. 7-Adam-19. attach. Code 3.

278
00:09:23.553 --> 00:09:26.020
[SIREN WAILING. ENGINE REVS]

279
00:09:26.022 --> 00:09:28.690
<i>Copy. 6-Mary-47 eastbound on Wilshire.</i>

280
00:09:28.692 --> 00:09:29.790
<i>approaching MacArthur Park.</i>

281
00:09:29.792 --> 00:09:30.858
That's right around the corner.

282
00:09:30.860 --> 00:09:31.893
[SIREN WAILING]

283
00:09:31.895 --> 00:09:34.228
Control. 7-Adam-07.
we're two blocks from there.

284
00:09:34.230 --> 00:09:35.897
<i>Suspect vehicle has crashed!</i>

285
00:09:35.899 --> 00:09:37.465
[TIRES SCREECH]

286
00:09:37.467 --> 00:09:39.534
[ENGINE REVS]

287
00:09:39.536 --> 00:09:41.903
♪♪

288
00:09:41.905 --> 00:09:43.004
[TIRES SCREECH]

289
00:09:43.006 --> 00:09:44.459
- Hey. get back! Get back!
- Hands! Hands!

290
00:09:44.461 --> 00:09:46.574
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- Show me your hands! Hands on the window!

291
00:09:46.576 --> 00:09:48.109
- Chris. get back!
- Hands! Hands!

292
00:09:48.111 --> 00:09:49.711
- Show me your hands!
- No! No!

293
00:09:50.780 --> 00:09:52.280
No! Chris!

294
00:09:52.282 --> 00:09:53.881
Son of a bitch!

295
00:09:53.883 --> 00:09:55.184
Rios!

296
00:09:56.419 --> 00:09:58.353
[TIRES SCREECHING]

297
00:09:59.422 --> 00:10:02.290
[SIREN WAILING]

298
00:10:02.292 --> 00:10:03.891
♪♪

299
00:10:03.893 --> 00:10:05.960
[TIRES SCREECHING]

300
00:10:05.962 --> 00:10:08.129
NOLAN: Control. 7-15.
we have the Maserati.

301
00:10:08.131 --> 00:10:09.263
northbound Park View.

302
00:10:09.265 --> 00:10:11.233
In pursuit. Speed's 60. Occupied once.

303
00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:14.699
LOPEZ: 7-Adam-07. shots fired.

304
00:10:14.701 --> 00:10:16.437
Officer down. Repeat. officer down.

305
00:10:16.439 --> 00:10:18.304
Requesting R.A. for a 25-year-old male.

306
00:10:18.306 --> 00:10:19.373
gunshot wound to the chest.

307
00:10:19.375 --> 00:10:20.842
- Come on. come on. come on!
- LOPEZ: Conscious and breathing.

308
00:10:20.844 --> 00:10:22.244
LOPEZ: Park View at 7th.

309
00:10:24.726 --> 00:10:27.521
DISPATCH: <i>All units. be
advised. 7-Adam-15 in pursuit</i>

310
00:10:27.523 --> 00:10:29.489
<i>of gray Maserati heading
south on Alvarado.</i>

311
00:10:29.491 --> 00:10:31.781
- Do you see him?
- Negative. I lost him at the last intersection.

312
00:10:31.783 --> 00:10:32.826
Damn it.

313
00:10:32.828 --> 00:10:33.950
FEMALE DISPATCH: <i>Attention. all units.</i>

314
00:10:33.952 --> 00:10:36.212
<i>Air-12 spotted a gray Maserati
matching suspect's vehicle</i>

315
00:10:36.214 --> 00:10:38.514
<i>entering covered parking
structure at 6th and Grand.</i>

316
00:10:38.516 --> 00:10:40.316
7-Adam-15 responding. Code 3.

317
00:10:40.318 --> 00:10:42.017
[SIREN WAILING]

318
00:10:42.019 --> 00:10:45.503
♪♪

319
00:10:45.505 --> 00:10:46.738
Just keep breathing. buddy. alright?

320
00:10:46.740 --> 00:10:48.043
- TIM: Martinez.
- Alright. Huh?

321
00:10:48.045 --> 00:10:50.251
Sarge is gonna want to talk
to you. You're a witness.

322
00:10:50.253 --> 00:10:51.876
- I'm not leaving this kid alone.
- I'll go.

323
00:10:51.878 --> 00:10:53.712
EMT: One. two. three! Lift!

324
00:10:53.714 --> 00:10:57.714
♪♪

325
00:10:59.820 --> 00:11:01.586
[ENGINE STARTS]

326
00:11:01.588 --> 00:11:04.490
[SIREN WAILING]

327
00:11:05.997 --> 00:11:08.097
This shouldn't have happened.

328
00:11:08.099 --> 00:11:09.999
I made a felony stop.

329
00:11:10.001 --> 00:11:12.535
Rios just charged.

330
00:11:12.537 --> 00:11:15.538
I mean. he's made mistakes
before. but never like this.

331
00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:17.006
He knows...

332
00:11:17.008 --> 00:11:19.210
stop at a safe distance.
wait for backup.

333
00:11:19.212 --> 00:11:21.595
- approach with caution. but...
- It hap... It happens.

334
00:11:21.597 --> 00:11:22.990
Rookies aren't used to the adrenaline.

335
00:11:22.992 --> 00:11:24.812
They get amped up. It's
lights and sirens syndrome.

336
00:11:24.814 --> 00:11:26.949
I told him on day one. I told him.

337
00:11:26.951 --> 00:11:29.986
It's the hardest part
about being a T.O. Okay?

338
00:11:29.988 --> 00:11:33.456
We drill it into their head.
but at the end of the day.

339
00:11:33.458 --> 00:11:34.758
they make their own calls.

340
00:11:36.061 --> 00:11:37.960
Still feels like my fault.

341
00:11:37.962 --> 00:11:39.606
No. Come on.

342
00:11:39.608 --> 00:11:41.298
- [GROANS]
- You hurt?

343
00:11:41.300 --> 00:11:43.615
Nah. I just... just tweaked
it pulling him out of danger.

344
00:11:43.617 --> 00:11:45.721
- I'm alright.
- 7-Adam-19.

345
00:11:45.723 --> 00:11:47.704
send an additional R.A. to my location.

346
00:11:47.706 --> 00:11:49.572
- [SIREN WAILING]
- JACKSON: You're gonna be okay.

347
00:11:49.574 --> 00:11:51.841
Look at me. Look at me. Alright?

348
00:11:51.843 --> 00:11:53.810
Remember the obstacle
course at the Academy?

349
00:11:53.812 --> 00:11:56.012
First time through.
you had a torn hamstring

350
00:11:56.014 --> 00:11:57.470
and still beat me.

351
00:11:57.472 --> 00:11:59.883
Yeah. and I practiced
every single day after that.

352
00:11:59.885 --> 00:12:01.107
knowing that you'd be coming for me.

353
00:12:01.109 --> 00:12:03.244
I was only number one because
you were there pushing me.

354
00:12:03.246 --> 00:12:05.722
And now I'm gonna be here pushing <i>you.</i>

355
00:12:05.724 --> 00:12:07.857
getting you back to your feet.

356
00:12:07.859 --> 00:12:08.891
Alright?

357
00:12:08.893 --> 00:12:10.827
Okay. and I expect your
"A" game. man. alright?

358
00:12:10.829 --> 00:12:12.695
None of that "I got shot" B.S.
You hear me?

359
00:12:12.697 --> 00:12:13.896
[MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY]

360
00:12:13.898 --> 00:12:15.031
Chris. you hear me. man?

361
00:12:15.033 --> 00:12:17.033
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

362
00:12:17.035 --> 00:12:19.091
- [ALARM BUZZING]
- He's losing too much blood!

363
00:12:19.093 --> 00:12:20.570
- How much further?!
- DRIVER: Three minutes out.

364
00:12:20.572 --> 00:12:22.872
JACKSON: Chris. Come on. Chris.
Stay with me. man! Come on!

365
00:12:22.874 --> 00:12:23.940
Chris!

366
00:12:23.942 --> 00:12:26.709
♪♪

367
00:12:26.711 --> 00:12:27.944
[TIRES SCREECH IN DISTANCE]

368
00:12:27.946 --> 00:12:29.045
There.

369
00:12:29.047 --> 00:12:32.915
♪♪

370
00:12:32.917 --> 00:12:34.083
[VEHICLE DOORS CLOSE]

371
00:12:34.085 --> 00:12:38.085
♪♪

372
00:12:40.125 --> 00:12:41.525
Nolan. Door.

373
00:12:42.627 --> 00:12:43.760
Got a gun.

374
00:12:43.762 --> 00:12:45.762
You need to secure it while
I go after the suspect.

375
00:12:45.764 --> 00:12:46.829
I'll go with you.

376
00:12:46.831 --> 00:12:48.765
No. that gun is a crucial
piece of evidence.

377
00:12:48.767 --> 00:12:51.093
and TID has their hands full
processing the shooting scene.

378
00:12:51.095 --> 00:12:53.264
so I am designating you the finder.

379
00:12:53.266 --> 00:12:54.771
Photograph everything.

380
00:12:54.773 --> 00:12:57.039
Make sure you get that gun
exactly how it was found.

381
00:12:57.041 --> 00:12:59.431
Glove up. collect it. and
store it in our shop's lock box.

382
00:12:59.433 --> 00:13:00.643
- You got it?
- Yes. ma'am.

383
00:13:00.645 --> 00:13:02.612
- [RADIO BEEPS]
- NOLAN: Control. 7-Adam-15.

384
00:13:02.614 --> 00:13:03.869
Suspect vehicle located

385
00:13:03.871 --> 00:13:06.285
in a parking structure on 6th and Grand.

386
00:13:06.287 --> 00:13:08.474
Gun on scene. My T.O.
is in pursuit of suspect

387
00:13:08.476 --> 00:13:11.120
through a maintenance door
on the northeast corner.

388
00:13:11.122 --> 00:13:12.955
- Need backup. Code 3.
- [RADIO BEEPS]

389
00:13:12.957 --> 00:13:16.659
[MACHINERY HISSING]

390
00:13:16.661 --> 00:13:20.661
♪♪

391
00:13:22.734 --> 00:13:26.102
[MACHINERY CLANKING]

392
00:13:26.104 --> 00:13:30.909
♪♪

393
00:13:32.911 --> 00:13:37.682
♪♪

394
00:13:39.684 --> 00:13:44.255
♪♪

395
00:13:46.157 --> 00:13:47.190
[FLASHLIGHT CLICKS]

396
00:13:47.192 --> 00:13:49.492
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Control. 7-Adam-15.

397
00:13:49.494 --> 00:13:51.099
Shut down all code 3 units.

398
00:13:51.101 --> 00:13:52.528
Suspect is G.O.A.

399
00:13:52.530 --> 00:13:53.830
- [RADIO BEEPS]
- Damn it.

400
00:13:53.832 --> 00:13:55.765
[MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY]

401
00:13:55.767 --> 00:13:56.943
NURSE LISA: 25-year-old male.

402
00:13:56.945 --> 00:13:58.667
single gunshot wound to the chest.

403
00:13:58.669 --> 00:14:01.464
Possible lung collapse. He's
down two liters of blood.

404
00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:02.522
Aren't you taking him to surgery?

405
00:14:02.524 --> 00:14:04.483
If I don't stop the bleeding.
he won't make it to the OR.

406
00:14:04.485 --> 00:14:06.186
Three. two. one.

407
00:14:06.978 --> 00:14:08.978
Get a gurney. Clear Trauma 1.

408
00:14:08.980 --> 00:14:10.546
Get him on the monitor.

409
00:14:10.548 --> 00:14:11.981
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

410
00:14:11.983 --> 00:14:14.617
Jackson. I hear... I heard
what happened. Is he... ?

411
00:14:14.619 --> 00:14:16.442
JACKSON: They're. um...
They're trying to stabilize him.

412
00:14:16.444 --> 00:14:17.566
He lost a lot of blood.

413
00:14:17.568 --> 00:14:19.055
- [CRYING] Oh. my God.
- No.

414
00:14:19.057 --> 00:14:20.857
Get it out.

415
00:14:20.859 --> 00:14:23.894
[CRYING]

416
00:14:24.828 --> 00:14:26.483
I have to go back to the station. okay?

417
00:14:26.485 --> 00:14:28.297
I got a mandatory callback. but...

418
00:14:28.299 --> 00:14:30.533
will you call me with any news?

419
00:14:30.535 --> 00:14:32.635
Of course. I'm... I'm
not going anywhere.

420
00:14:32.637 --> 00:14:34.303
[MONITORS BEEPING]

421
00:14:34.305 --> 00:14:36.807
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

422
00:14:39.711 --> 00:14:41.744
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

423
00:14:41.746 --> 00:14:43.179
[VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES. SIREN WAILING]

424
00:14:43.181 --> 00:14:44.547
Okay. scene's secure.

425
00:14:44.549 --> 00:14:46.215
What the hell are you doing?

426
00:14:46.217 --> 00:14:48.184
You holding something
in your right hand?

427
00:14:48.186 --> 00:14:49.218
Your gun hand?

428
00:14:49.220 --> 00:14:50.860
How many times I gotta tell you

429
00:14:50.862 --> 00:14:52.539
to keep your gun hand free at all times?

430
00:14:52.541 --> 00:14:53.589
Yeah. I know. I'm sorry.

431
00:14:53.591 --> 00:14:55.211
You've been on this job a whole
year. and you're still making

432
00:14:55.213 --> 00:14:57.326
the same dumb mistakes you've
been making since day one.

433
00:14:57.328 --> 00:14:58.594
You want to end up like Rios?

434
00:14:58.596 --> 00:14:59.862
Whoa. Tim.

435
00:14:59.864 --> 00:15:01.931
That's enough. man.

436
00:15:01.933 --> 00:15:02.965
Excuse me?

437
00:15:02.967 --> 00:15:04.634
You don't have to talk to her like that.

438
00:15:04.636 --> 00:15:05.668
She's my Boot.

439
00:15:05.670 --> 00:15:07.570
I'll talk to her however
the hell I want to

440
00:15:07.572 --> 00:15:10.202
so she doesn't end up eating
through a tube the rest of her life.

441
00:15:10.204 --> 00:15:11.337
You got that?

442
00:15:12.243 --> 00:15:13.510
Let's go. Boot.

443
00:15:15.786 --> 00:15:17.613
I did not need saving.

444
00:15:17.615 --> 00:15:19.916
[VEHICLE DOORS OPEN]

445
00:15:19.918 --> 00:15:21.083
[SIGHS]

446
00:15:21.085 --> 00:15:23.753
[VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES. CAMERA BEEPING]

447
00:15:23.755 --> 00:15:26.355
I kind of went overboard
with the crime scene photos.

448
00:15:26.357 --> 00:15:27.924
Better safe than sorry.

449
00:15:27.926 --> 00:15:30.127
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

450
00:15:35.767 --> 00:15:38.525
[VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES]

451
00:15:38.527 --> 00:15:39.682
No sign of the suspect?

452
00:15:39.684 --> 00:15:42.238
No. he got away clean. But
we did recover his weapon.

453
00:15:42.240 --> 00:15:43.639
Nine-mil. Recently fired.

454
00:15:43.641 --> 00:15:45.241
Good work. Anything else?

455
00:15:45.243 --> 00:15:48.058
Uh. yes. The car is
registered to a dealership...

456
00:15:48.060 --> 00:15:49.558
International Luxury Auto.

457
00:15:49.560 --> 00:15:51.714
- Stolen?
- Not reported.

458
00:15:51.716 --> 00:15:54.050
We need to run background checks
on the dealership employees.

459
00:15:54.052 --> 00:15:56.414
Already happening. But
we would get a much faster ID

460
00:15:56.416 --> 00:15:58.521
from the mobile fingerprint
unit inside your car.

461
00:15:58.523 --> 00:16:00.957
We pulled a clean print from
the driver's side window.

462
00:16:00.959 --> 00:16:03.060
Uh. yeah. Great.

463
00:16:10.301 --> 00:16:11.968
Any update on Chris?

464
00:16:11.970 --> 00:16:13.959
- Nothing yet.
- How is it out there?

465
00:16:13.961 --> 00:16:15.037
Controlled chaos.

466
00:16:15.039 --> 00:16:17.574
We're spread thin through two divisions.

467
00:16:21.346 --> 00:16:22.411
[DEVICE CHIRPS. BEEPS]

468
00:16:22.413 --> 00:16:25.982
And just like that.
our suspect has a name.

469
00:16:25.984 --> 00:16:28.985
Serj Derian. Number one on
Robbery-Homicide's hit list.

470
00:16:28.987 --> 00:16:30.152
Younger brother of Ruben.

471
00:16:30.154 --> 00:16:31.854
the head of the Derian crime family.

472
00:16:31.856 --> 00:16:33.656
Linked to drug trafficking. extortion.

473
00:16:33.658 --> 00:16:34.797
kidnapping. and murder.

474
00:16:34.799 --> 00:16:37.026
But so far. none of
the charges have stuck.

475
00:16:37.028 --> 00:16:40.329
Now. remember. this guy has
already shot one cop today.

476
00:16:40.331 --> 00:16:42.765
I need you focused. not angry.

477
00:16:42.767 --> 00:16:44.834
♪ Soldier. hold the fort down ♪

478
00:16:44.836 --> 00:16:47.837
♪ Yeah. I bet I burn that...
down before I pucker up ♪

479
00:16:47.839 --> 00:16:49.872
♪ Stuck on the cusp of a new
age of human consciousness ♪

480
00:16:49.874 --> 00:16:50.917
OFFICER: LAPD!

481
00:16:50.919 --> 00:16:54.010
Serj Derian. come out
with your hands up!

482
00:16:54.012 --> 00:16:57.013
♪ Name dropping the
dead finger to obelisk ♪

483
00:16:57.015 --> 00:17:00.282
♪ Insane. insane world ♪

484
00:17:00.284 --> 00:17:02.051
- LUCY: Clear!
- Clear!

485
00:17:02.053 --> 00:17:03.219
- Clear!
- Clear!

486
00:17:03.221 --> 00:17:05.121
- Clear!
- Clear!

487
00:17:05.123 --> 00:17:06.222
Clear!

488
00:17:06.224 --> 00:17:08.324
♪ Insane. insane world ♪

489
00:17:08.326 --> 00:17:09.358
He's not here.

490
00:17:09.360 --> 00:17:11.160
[VEHICLE DOORS CLOSE]

491
00:17:11.162 --> 00:17:12.261
Hey. you gotta go.

492
00:17:12.263 --> 00:17:14.063
I know. but how can I?

493
00:17:14.065 --> 00:17:15.197
Serj wasn't home.

494
00:17:15.199 --> 00:17:17.366
Bradford and Chen are
searching his stuff right now.

495
00:17:17.368 --> 00:17:18.834
What'd I miss?

496
00:17:18.836 --> 00:17:21.037
Harper has a custody
hearing in about an hour.

497
00:17:21.039 --> 00:17:22.672
and she's conflicted about leaving.

498
00:17:22.674 --> 00:17:25.741
but I say number-one priority
has to be getting Lila back.

499
00:17:25.743 --> 00:17:27.510
Tell me I'm right.

500
00:17:27.512 --> 00:17:28.744
100%.

501
00:17:28.746 --> 00:17:30.413
Look. take it from me.

502
00:17:30.415 --> 00:17:33.916
<i>Nothing</i> is more important than family.

503
00:17:33.918 --> 00:17:35.051
Alright. fine.

504
00:17:35.053 --> 00:17:37.286
But I will be back right after.

505
00:17:37.288 --> 00:17:38.354
Hey.

506
00:17:38.356 --> 00:17:40.861
Take my unmarked. I'll
ride back with Nolan.

507
00:17:40.863 --> 00:17:43.193
- Thanks.
- Give Lila a hug for me.

508
00:17:44.495 --> 00:17:46.863
[INDISTINCT TALKING IN DISTANCE]

509
00:17:48.232 --> 00:17:49.765
What are we looking for?

510
00:17:49.767 --> 00:17:51.521
[SIGHS] Anything that
could lead us to Serj.

511
00:17:51.523 --> 00:17:53.069
♪♪

512
00:17:53.071 --> 00:17:54.770
- What the hell?
- You got something?

513
00:17:54.772 --> 00:17:56.906
Yeah. a police report.

514
00:17:56.908 --> 00:17:58.141
LUCY: There's more.

515
00:17:59.210 --> 00:18:00.876
"Suspect... Serj Derian".

516
00:18:00.878 --> 00:18:02.378
His name's all over these.

517
00:18:02.380 --> 00:18:03.846
Someone inside the department

518
00:18:03.848 --> 00:18:05.948
has been feeding intel
to the Armenian mob.

519
00:18:05.950 --> 00:18:07.083
And by someone. you mean...

520
00:18:07.085 --> 00:18:08.118
A dirty cop.

521
00:18:10.142 --> 00:18:11.656
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

522
00:18:11.658 --> 00:18:13.181
SGT. GREY: Come in.

523
00:18:13.183 --> 00:18:14.283
Close the door.

524
00:18:16.790 --> 00:18:18.346
[DOOR CLOSES]

525
00:18:18.348 --> 00:18:21.983
So. Bradford and Chen just found
confidential police documents

526
00:18:21.985 --> 00:18:23.084
in Serj's home.

527
00:18:23.086 --> 00:18:27.423
Case files for LAPD
investigations into the Derians.

528
00:18:29.491 --> 00:18:31.565
You saying there's a mole
inside the department?

529
00:18:31.567 --> 00:18:34.234
It'd explain why these
guys have been so slippery.

530
00:18:34.236 --> 00:18:36.837
So. we haven't been able to
make a single case against them.

531
00:18:36.839 --> 00:18:38.295
What does internal affairs say?

532
00:18:38.297 --> 00:18:40.020
They're mobilizing.

533
00:18:40.022 --> 00:18:41.875
Commander West was keeping
it close to the vest.

534
00:18:41.877 --> 00:18:45.713
but I got a sense they already
have a few cops in mind.

535
00:18:45.715 --> 00:18:47.414
So. what do we do in the meantime?

536
00:18:47.416 --> 00:18:48.682
Serj's older brother... Ruben.

537
00:18:48.684 --> 00:18:49.717
[CLEARS THROAT]

538
00:18:49.719 --> 00:18:52.419
He runs things from
his house in Glendale.

539
00:18:52.421 --> 00:18:54.188
There's a chance Serj is holed up there.

540
00:18:54.190 --> 00:18:57.424
If not. Ruben's the first
person we should be questioning.

541
00:18:57.426 --> 00:18:58.983
Why are you only telling <i>me</i> all this?

542
00:18:58.985 --> 00:19:00.674
I know I can trust you.

543
00:19:00.676 --> 00:19:02.666
So I'm making you acting detective

544
00:19:02.668 --> 00:19:04.557
until this calms down.

545
00:19:04.559 --> 00:19:06.600
You already passed the
exam. so I might as well

546
00:19:06.602 --> 00:19:09.061
take advantage of you
until the brass realizes

547
00:19:09.063 --> 00:19:11.271
- what they're missing out on.
- Copy that.

548
00:19:11.273 --> 00:19:13.207
So. round up as many units as you need.

549
00:19:13.209 --> 00:19:15.702
call a judge for a
telephonic search warrant.

550
00:19:15.704 --> 00:19:17.405
Yes. sir.

551
00:19:20.616 --> 00:19:23.051
I've wanted this for
so long. so thank you.

552
00:19:23.819 --> 00:19:26.721
Just wish a cop didn't have
to get shot for it to happen.

553
00:19:28.457 --> 00:19:29.923
We answer the call when we get it.

554
00:19:29.925 --> 00:19:32.594
♪♪

555
00:19:36.632 --> 00:19:38.233
Still thinking about Grace?

556
00:19:39.402 --> 00:19:40.634
You're a good detective.

557
00:19:40.636 --> 00:19:41.835
[CHUCKLING] You're an easy case.

558
00:19:41.837 --> 00:19:44.438
Days like today just make you realize

559
00:19:44.440 --> 00:19:46.907
how little time you could have.

560
00:19:46.909 --> 00:19:48.609
Time I want to spend with <i>her.</i>

561
00:19:48.611 --> 00:19:51.051
That's the kind of thing you
might regret not telling someone.

562
00:19:52.861 --> 00:19:54.816
You know what? When
we get back to the station.

563
00:19:54.818 --> 00:19:56.483
I'm gonna book the evidence
and I'm gonna call her.

564
00:19:56.485 --> 00:19:57.584
<i>Call</i> her?

565
00:19:57.586 --> 00:19:59.246
You better get your ass over there

566
00:19:59.248 --> 00:20:00.481
and tell her in person.

567
00:20:01.490 --> 00:20:03.323
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

568
00:20:03.325 --> 00:20:06.360
They're putting together a
raid at Ruben Derian's house.

569
00:20:06.362 --> 00:20:07.494
Is Serj there?

570
00:20:07.496 --> 00:20:09.152
Only one way to find out.

571
00:20:09.154 --> 00:20:10.210
[RADIO BEEPS]

572
00:20:10.212 --> 00:20:13.500
Control. 7-Adam-15.
Attach us to that ATL.

573
00:20:13.502 --> 00:20:14.535
[RADIO BEEPS]

574
00:20:14.537 --> 00:20:16.571
[SIREN WAILS]

575
00:20:18.374 --> 00:20:19.506
[TIRES SCREECH]

576
00:20:19.508 --> 00:20:21.675
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

577
00:20:21.677 --> 00:20:24.344
- [VEHICLE DOORS CLOSE]
- MAN: Lock and load.

578
00:20:24.346 --> 00:20:25.612
Any eye on Serj?

579
00:20:25.614 --> 00:20:27.771
Not yet. but there's at least
a handful of unknowns inside.

580
00:20:27.773 --> 00:20:29.683
- What's the game plan?
- House is around the corner.

581
00:20:29.685 --> 00:20:31.985
I'll have officers cover the perimeter
while the rest of us breach.

582
00:20:31.987 --> 00:20:34.521
I would put Stapleton. Cole.
and Brady on the 3/4 corner.

583
00:20:34.523 --> 00:20:36.690
Jennings and Sanchez.
they can take the 2 side.

584
00:20:36.692 --> 00:20:38.493
We'll join you in the stack.

585
00:20:39.495 --> 00:20:40.527
[CHUCKLES]

586
00:20:40.529 --> 00:20:43.163
- Sorry. Second nature.
- All good. sir.

587
00:20:43.165 --> 00:20:45.532
You're the senior detective
on site. Operation is yours.

588
00:20:45.534 --> 00:20:46.723
Okay.

589
00:20:46.725 --> 00:20:47.801
Uh...

590
00:20:47.803 --> 00:20:48.836
You're acting detective?

591
00:20:48.838 --> 00:20:50.704
- For the day.
- Doing great.

592
00:20:50.706 --> 00:20:52.506
- Hey.
- Hey.

593
00:20:52.508 --> 00:20:54.408
Wish I was breaching with you guys.

594
00:20:54.410 --> 00:20:56.376
It'd feel good to subdue a
felon with force right now.

595
00:20:56.378 --> 00:20:57.711
Only temporarily.

596
00:20:57.713 --> 00:20:58.746
- Be safe.
- You too.

597
00:21:00.716 --> 00:21:02.316
- [BANGING ON DOOR]
- LOPEZ: Police! Open up!

598
00:21:02.318 --> 00:21:03.851
Hands up! Turn around!

599
00:21:03.853 --> 00:21:07.853
♪♪

600
00:21:11.601 --> 00:21:13.557
- Clear!
- Clear!

601
00:21:13.559 --> 00:21:14.661
Stand up!

602
00:21:14.663 --> 00:21:16.153
Hands on your head! Turn around!

603
00:21:16.155 --> 00:21:17.564
- [DOORS BANG]
- What can I do for you?

604
00:21:17.566 --> 00:21:19.867
We have a warrant to search
the premises for Serj Derian.

605
00:21:19.869 --> 00:21:21.155
[SIGHS] You could have just called.

606
00:21:21.157 --> 00:21:22.202
- [CHUCKLES]
- [HANDCUFFS CLICK]

607
00:21:22.204 --> 00:21:24.338
So much banging and
crashing just to discover

608
00:21:24.340 --> 00:21:26.273
that my brother didn't randomly drop by.

609
00:21:26.275 --> 00:21:27.641
All clear. No sign of Serj.

610
00:21:27.643 --> 00:21:30.344
Mr. Derian. we'd like you to come
with us to the station voluntarily.

611
00:21:30.346 --> 00:21:31.411
Yeah. you bet.

612
00:21:31.413 --> 00:21:33.480
Uh. look. why don't I meet
you guys down there. huh?

613
00:21:33.482 --> 00:21:34.548
There's only a half-hour left

614
00:21:34.550 --> 00:21:36.517
in what has been the
best game of the season.

615
00:21:36.519 --> 00:21:38.619
- It's zero-zero.
- A tactical master class.

616
00:21:38.621 --> 00:21:39.686
[REMOTE CLICKS]

617
00:21:39.688 --> 00:21:41.588
Your brother shot a cop.
You're coming with us now.

618
00:21:41.590 --> 00:21:42.689
On what charge?

619
00:21:42.691 --> 00:21:44.358
You're a material witness
to your brother's actions.

620
00:21:44.360 --> 00:21:46.608
and refusing to help could be construed

621
00:21:46.610 --> 00:21:48.428
- as aiding and abetting.
- Let's move.

622
00:21:48.430 --> 00:21:51.865
[PART CHIMP'S "DIRTY SUN" PLAYS]

623
00:21:51.867 --> 00:21:53.433
[FLATLINE]

624
00:21:53.435 --> 00:21:55.469
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

625
00:21:55.471 --> 00:21:58.305
♪♪

626
00:21:58.307 --> 00:22:00.407
- [PADDLES WHINE]
- GRACE: Clear.

627
00:22:00.409 --> 00:22:01.542
[PADDLES THUD]

628
00:22:01.544 --> 00:22:03.076
NURSE: Negative. No response.

629
00:22:03.078 --> 00:22:04.945
♪♪

630
00:22:04.947 --> 00:22:06.280
Alright. book the evidence.

631
00:22:06.282 --> 00:22:07.481
I'm gonna check and see what's next.

632
00:22:07.483 --> 00:22:08.582
Right.

633
00:22:08.584 --> 00:22:10.384
[VEHICLE DOORS CLOSE]

634
00:22:10.386 --> 00:22:14.386
♪♪

635
00:22:17.626 --> 00:22:18.759
[CLANK]

636
00:22:18.761 --> 00:22:22.761
♪♪

637
00:22:23.566 --> 00:22:24.731
Auto registration.

638
00:22:24.733 --> 00:22:27.000
And could I get a firearm tag?

639
00:22:27.002 --> 00:22:28.769
♪♪

640
00:22:28.771 --> 00:22:29.837
Wait a minute.

641
00:22:31.407 --> 00:22:32.773
W-Wait.

642
00:22:32.775 --> 00:22:34.074
Uh...

643
00:22:34.076 --> 00:22:37.578
Th... Uh. there was
a gun. There was. um...

644
00:22:37.580 --> 00:22:39.413
There's supposed to be a gun.

645
00:22:39.415 --> 00:22:43.317
[HEARTBEAT]

646
00:22:43.319 --> 00:22:44.418
Sorry.

647
00:22:44.420 --> 00:22:46.653
[HEARTBEAT QUICKENS]

648
00:22:46.655 --> 00:22:48.556
[HEARTBEAT QUICKENS]

649
00:22:51.026 --> 00:22:55.796
♪ Dirty light ♪

650
00:22:55.798 --> 00:22:58.799
♪♪

651
00:22:58.801 --> 00:23:01.835
♪ Like a ray of dirty sun ♪

652
00:23:01.837 --> 00:23:05.873
♪♪

653
00:23:06.675 --> 00:23:09.676
♪ Like a ray of dirty sun ♪

654
00:23:09.678 --> 00:23:11.678
♪♪

655
00:23:11.680 --> 00:23:17.551
♪ Go at the speed of dirty light ♪

656
00:23:17.553 --> 00:23:19.987
♪♪

657
00:23:19.989 --> 00:23:23.557
♪ Shine like a ray of dirty light ♪

658
00:23:23.559 --> 00:23:24.691
[DOOR CLOSES]

659
00:23:24.693 --> 00:23:26.994
Yeah. I understand. Thank you.

660
00:23:26.996 --> 00:23:29.129
[RECEIVER CLICKS]

661
00:23:29.131 --> 00:23:31.365
Sir. the weapon we
recovered from the Maserati.

662
00:23:31.367 --> 00:23:33.635
the gun that was used
to shoot Officer Rios.

663
00:23:34.703 --> 00:23:37.472
I secured it. and now it's missing.

664
00:23:39.682 --> 00:23:41.405
[SIGHS]

665
00:23:41.407 --> 00:23:44.645
That call was from the hospital.

666
00:23:44.647 --> 00:23:45.812
Chris Rios just died.

667
00:23:45.814 --> 00:23:48.148
♪♪

668
00:23:48.150 --> 00:23:51.885
That gun is now a murder weapon.

669
00:23:51.887 --> 00:23:53.053
And you lost it.

670
00:23:53.055 --> 00:23:55.590
♪♪

671
00:24:01.320 --> 00:24:03.320
CHEN: Can we talk about
what happened earlier?

672
00:24:04.775 --> 00:24:06.041
When earlier?

673
00:24:06.043 --> 00:24:07.409
With Emmett.

674
00:24:07.411 --> 00:24:08.777
There's nothing to say.

675
00:24:08.779 --> 00:24:10.479
The guy tried to tell
me how to do my job.

676
00:24:10.481 --> 00:24:12.414
On today of all days.

677
00:24:12.416 --> 00:24:14.206
I don't care if he's your boyfriend...

678
00:24:14.208 --> 00:24:15.964
He's not.

679
00:24:15.966 --> 00:24:18.022
Actually. he's a little
dead to me right now.

680
00:24:18.024 --> 00:24:20.732
You may be 30 days from
crossing the finish line.

681
00:24:20.734 --> 00:24:22.657
but the only thing that
happens when you cross it

682
00:24:22.659 --> 00:24:25.850
is that I won't be there to
keep you from washing out.

683
00:24:25.852 --> 00:24:27.308
Or worse.

684
00:24:27.310 --> 00:24:28.493
So you better believe

685
00:24:28.495 --> 00:24:30.496
this next month is gonna be tough.

686
00:24:32.266 --> 00:24:34.000
'Cause I know you can handle it.

687
00:24:37.271 --> 00:24:39.404
That's oddly sweet.

688
00:24:39.406 --> 00:24:41.740
But you're not the one
I'm mad at right now.

689
00:24:41.742 --> 00:24:43.242
I'm used to <i>you. I...</i>

690
00:24:43.244 --> 00:24:45.244
Okay. look.

691
00:24:45.246 --> 00:24:48.547
You are only gonna
hear me say this once.

692
00:24:48.549 --> 00:24:49.715
Emmett's a fireman.

693
00:24:49.717 --> 00:24:50.749
They're idiots.

694
00:24:50.751 --> 00:24:52.751
- [SCOFFS]
- But they mean well.

695
00:24:52.753 --> 00:24:54.286
And Emmett...

696
00:24:54.288 --> 00:24:55.420
[SIGHS]

697
00:24:55.422 --> 00:24:56.823
... he's a not-bad fireman.

698
00:24:57.949 --> 00:24:59.371
Don't write him off.

699
00:24:59.373 --> 00:25:02.242
I thought we weren't going
to discuss my personal life.

700
00:25:03.335 --> 00:25:04.874
We're friends.

701
00:25:04.876 --> 00:25:05.898
[CHUCKLES]

702
00:25:05.900 --> 00:25:07.633
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

703
00:25:07.635 --> 00:25:08.701
Hmm.

704
00:25:10.304 --> 00:25:11.370
Hey.

705
00:25:11.372 --> 00:25:15.607
♪♪

706
00:25:15.609 --> 00:25:17.609
[CRYING] Chris died.

707
00:25:17.611 --> 00:25:21.611
♪♪

708
00:25:23.751 --> 00:25:25.351
Oh. no.

709
00:25:27.588 --> 00:25:30.422
I can't leave you alone for a second.

710
00:25:30.424 --> 00:25:32.291
Hey. How was court? Did the judge...

711
00:25:32.293 --> 00:25:34.159
He's gonna make his
decision tomorrow morning.

712
00:25:34.161 --> 00:25:36.228
But how about we focus
on the murder weapon

713
00:25:36.230 --> 00:25:37.950
that went missing from the shop?

714
00:25:37.952 --> 00:25:41.166
Okay. you saw me bag it...

715
00:25:41.168 --> 00:25:43.402
and put it in the lock box.

716
00:25:43.404 --> 00:25:45.904
The only time we stopped
between the scene and the station

717
00:25:45.906 --> 00:25:47.606
was at Serj's house. for the raid.

718
00:25:47.608 --> 00:25:49.174
Could one of his guys have taken it?

719
00:25:49.176 --> 00:25:50.298
No. not possible.

720
00:25:50.300 --> 00:25:53.061
We had the perimeter completely
contained. and I locked the car.

721
00:25:53.063 --> 00:25:55.180
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

722
00:25:55.182 --> 00:25:57.559
Mostly sure. Almost mostly sure.

723
00:25:57.561 --> 00:26:00.463
Even if I didn't. it was
secured in the lock box.

724
00:26:01.655 --> 00:26:03.655
And there's no sign of forced entry.

725
00:26:03.657 --> 00:26:05.257
- None.
- You find the gun?

726
00:26:05.259 --> 00:26:07.159
No. and I don't think he's going to.

727
00:26:07.161 --> 00:26:08.226
Why?

728
00:26:08.228 --> 00:26:10.295
The lock box in the
shop wasn't broken into.

729
00:26:10.297 --> 00:26:12.931
but the key for the boxes
is universal across the LAPD.

730
00:26:12.933 --> 00:26:14.499
You think a cop took the gun?

731
00:26:14.501 --> 00:26:16.668
It's the only logical explanation.

732
00:26:16.670 --> 00:26:18.704
We know there's a dirty
cop connected to Serj.

733
00:26:18.706 --> 00:26:20.806
They must have heard on the
radio I'd secured the weapon.

734
00:26:20.808 --> 00:26:22.941
How long were you away from
the shop during the raid?

735
00:26:22.943 --> 00:26:24.543
Uh. we were. what. 20 minutes?

736
00:26:24.545 --> 00:26:26.645
More than enough time for
one of the officers involved

737
00:26:26.647 --> 00:26:27.946
to take the gun.

738
00:26:27.948 --> 00:26:29.881
It makes sense. but it's cold comfort.

739
00:26:29.883 --> 00:26:31.483
Even if we get the weapon back.

740
00:26:31.485 --> 00:26:33.285
the chain of custody has been destroyed.

741
00:26:33.287 --> 00:26:35.387
The D.A. can't use it to convict Serj

742
00:26:35.389 --> 00:26:37.356
for the murder of Officer Rios.

743
00:26:37.358 --> 00:26:38.657
If we ever find the guy.

744
00:26:38.659 --> 00:26:39.791
Oh. we'll find him.

745
00:26:39.793 --> 00:26:41.626
I'm calling all the
officers from the raid

746
00:26:41.628 --> 00:26:42.728
back to the station.

747
00:26:42.730 --> 00:26:44.167
Officer Lopez will be in charge

748
00:26:44.169 --> 00:26:45.697
of going through all
the body cam footage.

749
00:26:45.699 --> 00:26:46.798
What can we do?

750
00:26:46.800 --> 00:26:48.867
You and Armstrong can
take a run at Ruben Derian.

751
00:26:48.869 --> 00:26:50.702
See if we can sweat
something out of him.

752
00:26:50.704 --> 00:26:52.204
It'd be my pleasure.

753
00:26:52.206 --> 00:26:53.705
Alright. That's all.

754
00:26:53.707 --> 00:26:55.407
Hey. Sarge?

755
00:26:55.409 --> 00:26:57.809
Look. Officer Nolan
conducted himself admirably

756
00:26:57.811 --> 00:26:58.844
throughout the raid.

757
00:26:58.846 --> 00:27:00.545
I don't think he's to
blame for what happened.

758
00:27:00.547 --> 00:27:02.647
That'll be <i>my</i> call. Detective.

759
00:27:02.649 --> 00:27:04.383
I'll deal with it
when the time is right.

760
00:27:04.385 --> 00:27:05.507
Sir...

761
00:27:05.509 --> 00:27:06.885
Nolan.

762
00:27:06.887 --> 00:27:09.721
You do not want to have this
conversation with me right now.

763
00:27:09.723 --> 00:27:14.559
♪♪

764
00:27:14.561 --> 00:27:16.428
ARMSTRONG: Tell us about your brother.

765
00:27:16.430 --> 00:27:18.363
Serj? He's a nice guy.

766
00:27:18.365 --> 00:27:20.332
A bit of a free spirit.

767
00:27:20.334 --> 00:27:21.500
You two close?

768
00:27:21.502 --> 00:27:22.534
Sure.

769
00:27:22.536 --> 00:27:24.336
But I haven't seen him in a couple days.

770
00:27:24.338 --> 00:27:25.871
He takes off sometimes.

771
00:27:25.873 --> 00:27:27.129
Hm.

772
00:27:27.131 --> 00:27:28.440
Wanderlust.

773
00:27:28.442 --> 00:27:30.575
[CHUCKLES] Those Germans.

774
00:27:30.577 --> 00:27:32.577
They really have a word
for everything. don't they?

775
00:27:32.579 --> 00:27:34.513
But you reported his
car stolen this morning.

776
00:27:34.515 --> 00:27:36.381
An hour after it was used in an incident

777
00:27:36.383 --> 00:27:38.583
that ended with a dead police officer.

778
00:27:38.585 --> 00:27:40.585
The Maserati belongs to
the Derians' dealership.

779
00:27:40.587 --> 00:27:42.287
It was found missing during inventory.

780
00:27:42.289 --> 00:27:43.422
How convenient.

781
00:27:43.424 --> 00:27:45.690
Dozens of people have driven
that car in the past week.

782
00:27:45.692 --> 00:27:48.138
Now. my client has
been very cooperative.

783
00:27:48.140 --> 00:27:50.574
so if you don't have
any more questions...

784
00:27:51.698 --> 00:27:54.266
Alright. if you hear from
your brother. give us a call.

785
00:27:54.268 --> 00:27:55.700
He killed a cop.

786
00:27:55.702 --> 00:27:57.769
He is going to prison.

787
00:27:57.771 --> 00:27:59.304
It is up to you to decide

788
00:27:59.306 --> 00:28:01.773
whether or not you are going with him.

789
00:28:01.775 --> 00:28:03.242
I'll keep that in mind.

790
00:28:06.914 --> 00:28:09.714
[DOOR OPENS]

791
00:28:09.716 --> 00:28:11.483
- Now what?
- [DOOR CLOSES]

792
00:28:11.485 --> 00:28:14.545
We find a new way to flush
Serj out into the open.

793
00:28:14.547 --> 00:28:16.788
What the hell do you need
our body cams for. Sarge?

794
00:28:16.790 --> 00:28:18.457
SGT. GREY: Above your pay grade.

795
00:28:18.459 --> 00:28:19.525
Come on.

796
00:28:20.854 --> 00:28:21.987
Oh. hey. Cole.

797
00:28:22.896 --> 00:28:24.729
How you holding up?

798
00:28:24.731 --> 00:28:25.931
Not well.

799
00:28:25.933 --> 00:28:27.332
I should have said something.

800
00:28:27.334 --> 00:28:29.569
Hey. no. This... This is not your fault.

801
00:28:34.077 --> 00:28:35.599
LOPEZ: <i>House is around the corner.</i>

802
00:28:35.601 --> 00:28:37.085
<i>I'll have officers cover the perimeter</i>

803
00:28:37.087 --> 00:28:38.210
<i>while the rest of us breach.</i>

804
00:28:38.212 --> 00:28:40.412
<i>Okay. I would put Shelton.
Cole. and Boyd on the...</i>

805
00:28:40.414 --> 00:28:42.481
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

806
00:28:42.483 --> 00:28:46.118
[<i>CROWD CHEERING</i>]

807
00:28:46.120 --> 00:28:47.786
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

808
00:28:47.788 --> 00:28:50.589
ARMSTRONG: <i>We have a warrant to search
the premises for Serj Derian.</i>

809
00:28:50.591 --> 00:28:51.691
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

810
00:28:53.789 --> 00:28:54.811
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

811
00:28:54.813 --> 00:28:55.894
♪♪

812
00:28:55.896 --> 00:28:59.965
<i>Double-O-Smitty. At your service.</i>

813
00:28:59.967 --> 00:29:02.601
That man clearly does not know
the "on" button from the "off".

814
00:29:02.603 --> 00:29:04.436
[<i>SLURPS</i>]

815
00:29:04.438 --> 00:29:05.972
[GROANS]

816
00:29:07.841 --> 00:29:09.575
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

817
00:29:11.478 --> 00:29:13.945
♪♪

818
00:29:13.947 --> 00:29:16.481
[KNOCK ON DOOR. DOOR OPENS]

819
00:29:16.483 --> 00:29:18.884
Officer Erin Cole never switched
her camera on during the raid.

820
00:29:18.886 --> 00:29:20.936
She's a rookie. so it could
just be a mental error.

821
00:29:20.938 --> 00:29:23.159
Or she did it on purpose
to cover up taking the gun.

822
00:29:23.161 --> 00:29:24.523
Either way. we need to talk to her.

823
00:29:24.525 --> 00:29:27.012
I can reach out to her T.O..
call her back to the station.

824
00:29:27.014 --> 00:29:29.306
No need. Cole's ID badge
shows she's still here...

825
00:29:29.308 --> 00:29:30.364
in the locker room.

826
00:29:30.366 --> 00:29:34.366
♪♪

827
00:29:38.872 --> 00:29:40.839
She dumped everything that
we could use to trace her.

828
00:29:40.841 --> 00:29:41.841
She's running.

829
00:29:45.827 --> 00:29:47.661
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

830
00:29:47.663 --> 00:29:49.296
How was Officer Cole at the Academy?

831
00:29:49.298 --> 00:29:50.390
Solid.

832
00:29:50.392 --> 00:29:52.281
Yeah. she was a go-getter.

833
00:29:52.283 --> 00:29:54.429
I mean. she wasn't the
strongest or the fastest.

834
00:29:54.431 --> 00:29:56.086
but she made up for it with passion.

835
00:29:56.088 --> 00:29:57.227
I certainly wouldn't have flagged her

836
00:29:57.229 --> 00:29:58.866
as someone who'd betray the badge.

837
00:29:58.868 --> 00:30:00.554
- And as a rookie?
- Maybe she didn't turn.

838
00:30:00.556 --> 00:30:02.370
Maybe she was rotten from the onset.

839
00:30:02.372 --> 00:30:03.504
Meaning what?

840
00:30:03.506 --> 00:30:06.595
She was put into the
department by the Derian family

841
00:30:06.597 --> 00:30:07.697
as a mole?

842
00:30:10.980 --> 00:30:12.480
- Anything?
- SGT. GREY: No.

843
00:30:12.482 --> 00:30:14.215
No sign of Cole yet.

844
00:30:14.217 --> 00:30:17.218
An S.I.S. team conducted
a raid on her home

845
00:30:17.220 --> 00:30:18.953
and searched the home
of two family members.

846
00:30:18.955 --> 00:30:21.255
- Nothing.
- Forensic Accounting says there's been

847
00:30:21.257 --> 00:30:23.291
no financial activity
on any of her accounts.

848
00:30:23.293 --> 00:30:24.392
Well. she's a cop.

849
00:30:24.394 --> 00:30:26.059
Smart enough to know how
we're gonna try and catch her.

850
00:30:26.061 --> 00:30:29.263
And to know that every available
uniform will be looking for her.

851
00:30:29.265 --> 00:30:30.965
She'll probably flee to somewhere

852
00:30:30.967 --> 00:30:32.467
that's familiar to her.

853
00:30:32.469 --> 00:30:34.268
The question is. how will she get there?

854
00:30:34.270 --> 00:30:35.603
We put a BOLO out county-wide.

855
00:30:35.605 --> 00:30:37.438
The Sheriff's Department. Metro Transit.

856
00:30:37.440 --> 00:30:39.199
Port Police all been notified.

857
00:30:39.201 --> 00:30:41.210
- Eyes are open.
- John.

858
00:30:42.151 --> 00:30:43.985
Uh... excuse me.

859
00:30:45.141 --> 00:30:47.181
I'm so sorry about Officer Rios.

860
00:30:47.183 --> 00:30:48.216
Thank you.

861
00:30:48.218 --> 00:30:50.452
I know that you guys are
working through the night.

862
00:30:51.730 --> 00:30:54.455
I wasn't sure what to get...
I mean. dinner. breakfast?

863
00:30:54.457 --> 00:30:56.858
No. uh. no. pizza always plays.

864
00:30:56.860 --> 00:30:58.359
You guys want to grab this for the... ?

865
00:30:58.361 --> 00:30:59.428
Yeah.

866
00:31:02.265 --> 00:31:03.331
[SIGHS]

867
00:31:03.333 --> 00:31:05.366
Anyway. I mean. I-I know you're busy.

868
00:31:05.368 --> 00:31:07.202
[SIGHS]

869
00:31:08.171 --> 00:31:10.211
I just want you to know
that I'm thinking about you.

870
00:31:11.341 --> 00:31:12.941
I'm thinking about you. too.

871
00:31:14.844 --> 00:31:16.878
Um...

872
00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:18.546
thank you so much for the food.

873
00:31:18.548 --> 00:31:20.014
Uh...

874
00:31:20.016 --> 00:31:21.083
talk soon?

875
00:31:22.018 --> 00:31:23.218
Yeah.

876
00:31:25.355 --> 00:31:27.054
Bye.

877
00:31:27.056 --> 00:31:31.093
♪♪

878
00:31:31.995 --> 00:31:34.228
Hey. Everything okay?

879
00:31:34.230 --> 00:31:37.035
Um. no. But that's a
problem for another day.

880
00:31:37.037 --> 00:31:39.305
Right now. we need to find Erin.

881
00:31:41.137 --> 00:31:42.503
LUCY: What are you looking at?

882
00:31:42.505 --> 00:31:45.006
I'm just going over all
her social media accounts.

883
00:31:45.008 --> 00:31:46.750
I'm just hoping to
find something in here

884
00:31:46.752 --> 00:31:49.053
that'll give us a clue
as to where she went.

885
00:31:49.979 --> 00:31:51.345
I just don't get it.

886
00:31:51.347 --> 00:31:53.648
She's so happy and carefree.

887
00:31:53.650 --> 00:31:55.650
W-What could happen to make her do this?

888
00:31:55.652 --> 00:31:58.477
Yeah. I mean. social media
shows the side of us

889
00:31:58.479 --> 00:32:00.113
that we <i>want people to see.</i>

890
00:32:01.891 --> 00:32:03.524
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

891
00:32:03.526 --> 00:32:04.559
"#RVlife".

892
00:32:04.561 --> 00:32:06.494
The other night at the bar.

893
00:32:06.496 --> 00:32:09.019
Erin said she wanted to
go on a road trip in an RV

894
00:32:09.021 --> 00:32:10.665
just as soon as the
Thirty Day Push was over.

895
00:32:10.667 --> 00:32:12.066
You think that's her escape plan?

896
00:32:12.068 --> 00:32:13.501
It would give her mobility.

897
00:32:13.503 --> 00:32:15.336
It would give her a place
to hide off the grid.

898
00:32:15.338 --> 00:32:18.406
[DISTORTED PONY'S "DEATH
IN THE TURNSTILE" PLAYS]

899
00:32:18.408 --> 00:32:22.408
♪♪

900
00:32:28.465 --> 00:32:30.855
- [RADIO BEEPS]
- NOLAN: The house the RV is registered to

901
00:32:30.857 --> 00:32:32.042
is at the end of this street.

902
00:32:32.044 --> 00:32:33.087
- On our go.
- [RADIO BEEPS]

903
00:32:33.089 --> 00:32:35.089
I hope she surrenders without a fight.

904
00:32:35.091 --> 00:32:36.223
I wouldn't count on it.

905
00:32:36.225 --> 00:32:37.625
If she's in deep with the Derians.

906
00:32:37.627 --> 00:32:40.428
she knows they'll kill her
to keep her from talking.

907
00:32:40.430 --> 00:32:42.998
[TIRES SCREECH]

908
00:32:44.210 --> 00:32:45.232
She's on the move!

909
00:32:45.234 --> 00:32:46.934
[RV ENGINE REVS]

910
00:32:46.936 --> 00:32:48.369
Watch out. Watch out!

911
00:32:48.371 --> 00:32:50.672
[TIRES SCREECH]

912
00:32:51.975 --> 00:32:53.240
Control. 7-Adam-15.

913
00:32:53.242 --> 00:32:55.943
We just got 245'd by
suspect Cole in an RV.

914
00:32:55.945 --> 00:32:57.712
Beige RV. Arizona plates.

915
00:32:57.714 --> 00:33:01.148
Alpha-Bravo-7-9. heading north
on Mission Road towards 1st.

916
00:33:01.150 --> 00:33:03.584
[SIRENS WAILING]

917
00:33:03.586 --> 00:33:05.720
♪♪

918
00:33:05.722 --> 00:33:07.154
[ENGINE REVS]

919
00:33:07.156 --> 00:33:11.156
♪♪

920
00:33:16.599 --> 00:33:20.599
♪♪

921
00:33:26.175 --> 00:33:27.475
Look out.

922
00:33:27.477 --> 00:33:31.477
♪♪

923
00:33:33.616 --> 00:33:37.616
♪♪

924
00:33:39.689 --> 00:33:41.288
Whoa!

925
00:33:41.290 --> 00:33:45.290
♪♪

926
00:33:47.664 --> 00:33:48.763
Look out!

927
00:33:48.765 --> 00:33:50.154
[CLATTER]

928
00:33:50.156 --> 00:33:51.666
She's gonna go through.
She's not gonna stop.

929
00:33:51.668 --> 00:33:53.200
♪♪

930
00:33:53.202 --> 00:33:54.436
[METAL CREAKS]

931
00:33:56.339 --> 00:33:58.339
[TIRES SCREECH]

932
00:33:58.341 --> 00:34:01.642
♪♪

933
00:34:01.644 --> 00:34:02.777
DISPATCH: <i>Attention. all units.</i>

934
00:34:02.779 --> 00:34:05.046
Air-16 tracking suspect vehicle

935
00:34:05.048 --> 00:34:08.482
<i>heading east on Colorado
towards Pasadena.</i>

936
00:34:08.484 --> 00:34:12.484
♪♪

937
00:34:18.361 --> 00:34:19.546
- Clear.
- NOLAN: Clear.

938
00:34:19.548 --> 00:34:20.753
- What do we got?
- HARPER: She's on foot.

939
00:34:20.755 --> 00:34:22.450
- Couple minutes ahead.
- Alright. head inside.

940
00:34:22.452 --> 00:34:24.131
Split up. She could be anywhere.

941
00:34:24.133 --> 00:34:26.300
♪♪

942
00:34:26.302 --> 00:34:28.636
Control. suspect is on foot.
Rose Bowl Stadium.

943
00:34:28.638 --> 00:34:30.237
Requesting backup and airship.

944
00:34:30.239 --> 00:34:34.239
♪♪

945
00:34:37.814 --> 00:34:41.814
♪♪

946
00:34:45.555 --> 00:34:49.555
♪♪

947
00:34:53.229 --> 00:34:57.229
♪♪

948
00:35:00.837 --> 00:35:04.837
♪♪

949
00:35:08.578 --> 00:35:10.411
[PANTING]

950
00:35:10.413 --> 00:35:11.446
Erin!

951
00:35:12.606 --> 00:35:14.129
[ECHOING] Erin!

952
00:35:14.131 --> 00:35:15.353
Drop that gun right now!

953
00:35:15.355 --> 00:35:17.218
[VOICE BREAKING] I can't.

954
00:35:17.220 --> 00:35:19.220
Come on. Erin.

955
00:35:19.222 --> 00:35:21.589
It's me. You know me.

956
00:35:21.591 --> 00:35:23.724
We've been through a lot
together. You can talk to me.

957
00:35:23.726 --> 00:35:25.193
Just talk to me.

958
00:35:26.388 --> 00:35:28.444
I never wanted this.

959
00:35:28.446 --> 00:35:30.264
I know.

960
00:35:30.266 --> 00:35:32.433
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

961
00:35:32.435 --> 00:35:35.202
I had problems.

962
00:35:35.204 --> 00:35:38.239
Debts. and... they paid them.

963
00:35:38.241 --> 00:35:40.741
And [EXHALES SHARPLY]
and then they owned me.

964
00:35:40.743 --> 00:35:42.243
Who did?

965
00:35:42.245 --> 00:35:43.377
The Derians?

966
00:35:43.379 --> 00:35:45.446
I finally paid them back.

967
00:35:45.448 --> 00:35:46.881
and I told Serj I was done.

968
00:35:46.883 --> 00:35:49.116
but he... he pulled a gun

969
00:35:49.118 --> 00:35:51.452
and he tried to kill me
when I wouldn't scare and...

970
00:35:51.454 --> 00:35:53.320
The shots fired call.

971
00:35:53.322 --> 00:35:55.122
Serj. he... he got caught flat-footed.

972
00:35:55.124 --> 00:35:58.425
and he... he jumped
in the Maserati. and...

973
00:35:58.427 --> 00:36:00.628
Chris is dead because of me. [SOBS]

974
00:36:00.630 --> 00:36:03.831
No. no. no! Wait. no! Don't! Just...

975
00:36:03.833 --> 00:36:06.634
It doesn't have to all be for nothing.

976
00:36:06.636 --> 00:36:09.770
Okay. you can start to make this right.

977
00:36:09.772 --> 00:36:10.938
Just...

978
00:36:10.940 --> 00:36:13.250
♪♪

979
00:36:13.252 --> 00:36:15.075
... name names.

980
00:36:15.077 --> 00:36:16.600
Okay? Just testify.

981
00:36:16.602 --> 00:36:19.237
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

982
00:36:20.197 --> 00:36:21.297
- Armstrong.
- No!

983
00:36:22.585 --> 00:36:23.585
[THUD]

984
00:36:29.659 --> 00:36:34.264
♪♪

985
00:36:36.966 --> 00:36:38.065
[RADIO BEEPS]

986
00:36:38.067 --> 00:36:41.502
Control. uh. requesting an R.A. unit.

987
00:36:41.504 --> 00:36:42.870
[VOICE BREAKING] 25-year-old female.

988
00:36:42.872 --> 00:36:44.371
multiple gunshot wounds to the chest.

989
00:36:44.373 --> 00:36:45.773
[SIGHS]

990
00:36:45.775 --> 00:36:46.874
Not conscious. not breathing.

991
00:36:46.876 --> 00:36:48.375
[RADIO BEEPS]

992
00:36:48.377 --> 00:36:52.377
♪♪

993
00:37:00.096 --> 00:37:01.761
SGT. GREY: I know you're all exhausted.

994
00:37:02.861 --> 00:37:08.164
The past twenty-four hours have
brought a... lot of heartache.

995
00:37:08.166 --> 00:37:10.300
You did great work out there.

996
00:37:10.302 --> 00:37:11.735
Remember that.

997
00:37:11.737 --> 00:37:14.671
I was notified that
Rios's memorial service

998
00:37:14.673 --> 00:37:15.773
is Saturday afternoon.

999
00:37:18.043 --> 00:37:19.709
Go home. get some rest.

1000
00:37:19.711 --> 00:37:21.878
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

1001
00:37:21.880 --> 00:37:23.580
Nolan.

1002
00:37:23.582 --> 00:37:24.988
I'm gonna need you to stay behind.

1003
00:37:24.990 --> 00:37:26.679
IA is requesting your statement

1004
00:37:26.681 --> 00:37:28.143
while it's still fresh in your mind.

1005
00:37:28.145 --> 00:37:29.212
Yes. sir.

1006
00:37:32.224 --> 00:37:33.624
- [DOOR OPENS]
- Hey.

1007
00:37:36.561 --> 00:37:38.061
- You okay?
- [DOOR CLOSES]

1008
00:37:38.063 --> 00:37:40.063
[GEOGRAPHER'S "GET THERE SOON" PLAYS]

1009
00:37:40.065 --> 00:37:42.065
I thought I had a chance
at getting through to her.

1010
00:37:42.067 --> 00:37:46.069
♪♪

1011
00:37:46.071 --> 00:37:47.203
I had no choice.

1012
00:37:47.205 --> 00:37:49.606
Oh. I...

1013
00:37:49.608 --> 00:37:50.941
I know.

1014
00:37:52.611 --> 00:37:54.210
Just such a waste.

1015
00:37:54.212 --> 00:37:57.080
♪♪

1016
00:37:57.082 --> 00:37:58.115
[DOOR OPENS]

1017
00:38:00.619 --> 00:38:02.585
[KEYS JINGLE]

1018
00:38:02.587 --> 00:38:04.555
You want me to make you some tea?

1019
00:38:05.857 --> 00:38:07.124
I'm okay.

1020
00:38:08.260 --> 00:38:09.926
♪ Find the light ♪

1021
00:38:09.928 --> 00:38:11.628
Come here.

1022
00:38:11.630 --> 00:38:14.698
